        "unit": "dimensionless L2 norm"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/sensitivity-analysis-geometry",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Geometric sensitivity analysis for worst-case hemolysis identification",
      "description": "Parametric CFD study across 18 geometry variants spanning ±10% tolerance envelope on 4 critical dimensions (impeller tip clearance, volute gap, inlet diameter, blade angle). Latin hypercube sampling used to select geometry combinations. Worst-case hemolysis identified at minimum tip clearance and maximum volute gap combination. Results confirm CFD model is sensitive to relevant geometric parameters and can reliably rank-order hemolysis risk across variants."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/turbulence-model-assessment",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Turbulence model sensitivity and validation for blood pump flows",
      "description": "Three turbulence closures evaluated: k-omega SST, realizable k-epsilon, and RSM. Comparison against PIV velocity measurements in the FDA pump benchmark geometry (ASME V&V 40 Appendix data). k-omega SST demonstrated best agreement with experimental velocity profiles (mean relative error 6.1% vs 11.3% and 14.7% for the other models). k-omega SST selected as primary model. Hemolysis index sensitivity to turbulence model selection quantified at ±12% across the three models.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": {
