      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver verified against at least one analytical benchmark relevant to the flow regime.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent verified against Poiseuille flow (L2 error 0.31%) and lid-driven cavity benchmark (Re=1000, L2 error 1.2%). Both benchmarks are relevant to the laminar-transitional flow regime encountered in the CPB pump at clinical operating conditions. Verification results documented in VVR-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% on QoI for the production mesh.",
      "rationale": "GCI study performed on three systematically refined meshes. Fine-mesh GCI of 3.2% for hemolysis index QoI, exceeding the required threshold. Observed order of convergence p=1.94 confirms asymptotic convergence regime. Production mesh (5.8M elements) used for all parametric studies to balance accuracy and computational cost."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions sufficiently documented and reproducible for validation comparison.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic pump benchmark experimental conditions fully documented in Stewart et al. (2012) and ASME V&V 40 appendix data package. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, viscosity 3.5 cP) properties, inlet flow rates, rotational speeds, and temperature (37°C) all specified. Operating points span the clinical CPB range of 3–6 L/min at 2500–3500 RPM."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mean absolute relative error on NIH < 15% across all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD NIH predictions compared against experimental measurements at 5 operating points. Mean absolute relative error of 8.4%, well within the 15% acceptance threshold. Individual point errors range from 2.1% to 13.7%. No systematic bias observed across the flow-speed matrix. Acceptance criterion satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly link to clinical hemolysis endpoint and regulatory acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), the standard regulatory metric for pump-induced blood damage. Secondary QoI is relative hemolysis index (RH) comparing device to predicate, which is the direct acceptance criterion (RH < 1). Both QoIs are directly linked to the clinical endpoint of hemolysis-related adverse events and are recognized by FDA guidance for CPB device submissions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry and operating conditions sufficiently representative of the COU device and clinical use envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which shares impeller topology and operating regime with the subject CPB device. Operating conditions span the clinical use envelope. Blood analog fluid properties match those used in predicate device hemolysis testing. Geometric differences between validation and subject device are within the parametric sensitivity study envelope, supporting extrapolation of validation findings."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual convergence criteria met; mass and momentum conservation verified.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to residual levels below 1e-5 for continuity and momentum equations. Mass imbalance across inlet-outlet boundaries less than 0.01% in all cases. Convergence monitored via NIH QoI stabilization over final 500 iterations; variation less than 0.5% confirming solution stationarity."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary conditions and material properties verified.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup performed by senior CFD analyst not involved in original setup. Boundary conditions, material properties, mesh quality metrics, and solver settings all verified against the documented simulation plan. No discrepancies identified. Review documented in QA-CFD-2024-017."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Governing equations appropriate for the flow regime; constitutive model for blood rheology justified.",
      "rationale": "Reynolds-averaged Navier-Stokes with k-omega SST turbulence closure selected based on turbulence model sensitivity study showing best agreement with PIV benchmark data. Blood treated as Newtonian fluid (viscosity 3.5 cP) consistent with high-shear CPB operating conditions where non-Newtonian effects are negligible. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model applied as standard for CFD hemolysis prediction in regulatory submissions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs traceable to measurement data or published sources with uncertainty characterization.",
      "rationale": "Geometry inputs derived from CAD with dimensional tolerances ±0.05 mm. Fluid properties from ASTM F1841 blood analog specification. Boundary conditions (flow rates, rotational speeds) from clinical operating envelope documentation. Input uncertainty propagated through parametric study. All inputs documented in simulation data package SDP-CPB-2024."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2 for computational-only study without physical test samples in scope.",
      "rationale": "This factor addresses physical test sample representativeness. The validation dataset used is the FDA generic pump benchmark, which employed standardized blood analog fluid per ASTM F1841. Sample preparation and fluid characterization were performed by the original investigators and are documented in the published benchmark dataset. No additional test samples were prepared for this study; the factor is not assessed at MRL 2 as physical testing is outside the scope of this computational study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; parameter equivalency between validation and COU addressed qualitatively.",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between the validation geometry (FDA generic pump) and the subject CPB device is addressed qualitatively through the relevance of validation activities assessment. Quantitative equivalency mapping is not required at MRL 2. Key parameters (impeller diameter, tip clearance range, operating flow-speed envelope) are within ±20% of validation geometry, supporting qualitative equivalency judgment."
    }
  ],
